Differential diagnosis.
This species can be distinguished from others in the genus by its smaller size, the salt-and-pepper coloration of the fore and middle tibiae (
Fig. 15C
), the large spot on the side of the first abdominal tergite (
Fig. 15A–C
) and the absence of spots on the tegmina.

General.
Size small for genus (
Table 5
). Stance in nature distinctive (
Fig. 15C
).

